fields.description:
Every deployment, the NGINX Splunk config is lost and requires replacement. This has been a known problem which we would like fixed.

Our current remedial instructions are as follows:

ls /etc/nginx/sites-enabled
eventhub_server    gaz               _logformats  mps_proxies       sarreporting         server-webservices  upstream-restservices  upstream-webservices
eventhub_upstream  internal-servers  mps          riak_loadbalance  server-restservices  ssl_listener upstream_splunk
If upstream_splunk is red, then this indicates that the file it is linked to in /etc/nginx/sites-available does not exist.

sudo vi /etc/nginx/sites-available/upstream_splunk   (enter the lines below)
upstream splunk  {
    server localhost:8000;
}
save and close the file and then

ls /etc/nginx/sites-enabled
The file should now be blue like all of the other files in that directory

The main UI service needs to be validated

sudo vi /etc/nginx/sites-available/server-webservices   (search for splunk)
If no entry can be found then enter the text below at the bottom of the file

 location /splunk  {
    proxy_pass  http://splunk;
    proxy_redirect off;

    proxy_set_header  Host $host;
    proxy_set_header  X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    proxy_set_header  X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    types {application/x-javascript              js;}
    allow all;
  }
Ensure the file finishes with a } and save and close the file.

Ensure the file permissions of the amended files are correct

sudo chown -R nginx:spineii-applications /etc/nginx/sites-available/
sudo chown -R nginx:spineii-applications /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
Restart Nginx to reload the configuration and then try to access Splunk again

sudo service nginx restart
